cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about understanding the generalization of deep learning models, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on the landscape of the loss function and how it affects the generalization capability of deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
